{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5150c2fa-7139-4812-94b6-c6a64ac92f87","content":"To switch to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC), you need to make these changes:\n\n**1. On nuget.org:**\n- Go to your package's settings → \"Manage trusted publishers\"\n- Add a GitHub Actions publisher (owner, repo, branch/environment)\n\n**2. In your workflow:**\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write  # Required for OIDC token\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      # build/pack steps...\n      - name: Push to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n- Add `permissions: id-token: write`\n- Remove `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` from the push command\n- The `dotnet nuget push` command will automatically use the OIDC token when no API key is provided and the id-token permission is granted\n- You can delete the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret once verified\n\n**Optional but recommended:** Use a GitHub Environment (e.g., `production`) for deployment protection rules, and reference it in the trusted publisher config on nuget.org.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b1b28447-87ab-4016-86a6-c5088cb1b413","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about switching from using a NuGet API key (stored as a secret) to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC) in their GitHub Actions publish workflow. This is a general knowledge question about GitHub Actions and NuGet publishing - I don't need to look at any specific files since there's no repository here.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about what needs to change.","outputTokens":410,"requestId":"1410:2BEA6E:1C9B793:1FABDA9:69FA9057"},"id":"b844fc17-2b32-4ca2-8430-38505f7661c8","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:50:40.796Z","parentId":"3cbf5c76-bea8-4cc6-80d3-f536d57a2985"}
